      "message": "[Medium] Line 52: 🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider: Switching the call-notification gate from delivered `priority` to `originalPriority` means downgraded FCM messages are still treated as high-priority calls. On Android, foreground-service start exemptions depend on the delivered priority; if FCM downgraded the message, this can trigger avoidable `ForegroundServiceStartNotAllowedException` paths and still run call wake/reconnect logic for a message the OS no longer considers high priority. Keep the foreground-service decision based on delivered priority, and use a separate call-type predicate for the connectivity restriction if needed.\n```suggestion\nval isCallPush \u003d pushType.contains(\"audioCall\") || pushType.contains(\"videoCall\")\nval isHighPriorityCallNotification \u003d isCallPush \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.priority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\n\nif (isHighPriorityCallNotification) {\n```\nThen gate `connectivityChanged()` with the intended priority semantics explicitly.",
